GDF Suez Negotiating Asset Merger With Duke Energy, Valor Says

-- B y   J u a n   P a b l o   S p i n e t t o
-- 
2011-06-28T12:38:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-28/gdf-suez-negotiating-asset-merger-with-duke-energy-valor-says.html
GDF Suez (GSZ)  SA is in talks to combine
its Latin American assets with  Duke Energy Corp. (DUK)  in a deal worth
30 billion reais ($18.8 billion), newspaper Valor Economico
reported, citing unidentified people close to the negotiations.  Paris-based GDF Suez may control between 60 percent and 70
percent of the new company and Duke the remainder, the newspaper
said. The company would have a combined capacity of 15,000
megawatts, according to the Sao Paulo-based newspaper.  Duke’s press office declined to comment when contacted by
Valor, the newspaper said. Executives of GDF weren’t available
for comment, Valor said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Juan Pablo Spinetto in Rio de Janeiro at 
 jspinetto@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dale Crofts at   dcrofts@bloomberg.net  